<TITLE> Stocks open higher </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 18 (bdnews24.com)  Dhaka stocks rose steeply in the opening hour Tuesday and although the benchmark index declined in the second hour of trading, it recovered and continued to gain during midday session. The DGEN or general index at 11:39am was at 2982.20, up 16.63 points or 0.56 percent. The DSI or all share price index rose 12.81 points or 0.51 percent at 2512.84. Of the issues traded, 87 gained, 65 lost and 16 held steady. Turnover was at Tk 537.099 million from trading of 1,574,223 shares. At 11:39am UCBL emerged at the peak of the top share board by value. It was selling at Tk 4698 from Monday's Tk 4592.75. BRAC Bank, one of the most active shares, was selling higher at Tk 1639 from Tk 1634 the previous day. Exim Bank, however, was selling down at Tk 395 from Monday's closing price of Tk 395.75. AB Bank was selling at Tk 2610 from Tk 2624.75 the previous day. Market major Summit Power rose to Tk 1482.5 from Monday's Tk 1481. Other scrips among the top share board by value, Prime Bank, Islami Bank, NBL, Uttara Bank and Lafarge Surma Cement also rose. bd
